string.stringId: Steam Lobby Display List works with Heathen Lobby Hunter to facilitate browsing and quick join of lobbies. Steam Lobby Display List its self simply listens for Heathen Lobby Hunter browse events and constructs a list of available lobbies from the result. The main body of work is handled by Heathen Lobby Hunter which manages the flow of searches and lists against the Heathen Steam Lobby Manager. Heathen Lobby Hunter exposes several forms of search and create including: Quick Match: Performs a search with an decreasingly strict argument over an increasignly wide area untill a match is found with an option Create Lobby operation if all options are exhasted. Browse: Performs a search and compiles a detailed list of results for use in UI componenets. Create Private: Creates a private lobby with matching filter data. Create Public: Creates a public lobby with matching filter data. Create Friends Only: Creates a friends only lobby with matching filter data. Create Invisible: Creates an invisible lobby with matching filter data. Heathen Lobby Hunter exposes settings and events that facilitate immediate and delayed server creation. For example if you want your game server to be made available immedatly vs waiting untill the lobby is full or On Demand which requires the host to Establish Server when read.
